"{\"content\":{\"body\":\"Spanish farmers [have warned](https://www.coagandalucia.com/index.php/actualidad/item/la-brutal-subida-de-los-costes-anticipa-significativos-recortes-de-produccion-en-el-campo-espanol) agriculture production costs are skyrocketing and want \\\"urgent\\\" help from the national and regional governments to stop producers being crushed by wholesale buyers trying to keep prices in supermarkets down.\\n\\nCOAG says the \\\"brutal\\\" rise in price will lead to \\\"significant production cuts in the Spanish countryside\\\".\\n\\nThe farming organistion says electricity prices are up 300%, fertilizers up 100%, diesel up 40-60%, plastics up 50%, water up 30% and animal feeds up 25%.\\n\\nThey estimate the cost of bringing a truck of fertilizer online in a field has gone up from €4,000 last year to €8,000-10,000 now.\\n\\n\\\"In the case of olive irrigation, the electricity bill has gone up €160 a hectare, which means an average plantation (25 hectares) is looking at a €4,000 rise compared to last year.\\\"\\n\\n\\\"A gauge of western European prices for ammonia, used to make nitrogen fertilizer, surged to a 13-year high to $910 a metric ton\\\", reported [The Independent](https://www.independent.ie/business/farming/news/farming-news/fertilizer-prices-are-getting-more-expensive-in-europe-adding-to-food-inflation-concerns-41004224.html), citing natural gas prices as the driving force. [This](https://twitter.com/f_wintersberger/status/1454708782932582406) is what that looks like in a graph.\\n\\nFertilizer prices in the United States [are also](https://twitter.com/GreenMarkets1/status/1450137251741159424) at record levels. Globally, food price indices [rose](https://twitter.com/matthewbennett/status/1453713683612258307) to their highest level since 2011 in September, with an especially significant rise in the price of vegetable oils.\\n\\nThe general annual inflation rate in Spain [rose](https://twitter.com/matthewbennett/status/1453696816545927172) to 5.5% in October, its highest level since August 1992.\\n\\nOn Sunday night, Algeria [closed](https://www.rtve.es/noticias/20211101/argelia-cierra-gasoducto-magreb-europa/2211040.shtml) the gas pipeline that runs through Morocco to Spain. Plan B involves bringing part of Spain's natural gas supply from the North African country over on ships.\\n\\nHow long will these prices rises take to reach Spanish supermarkets? How will farmers and farm workers struggle and react in the meantime, this coming winter?\\n\\n**Guarantee independent journalism here:** https://www.thespainreport.es/value/guarantee \",\"timestamp\":1635882027,\"title\":\"Spanish farmers warn on agriculture inflation\"},\"digest\":\"Ou06yHhWM4A1m8czKZcbYM7-_GS1nRSD55e-JqrLCEw\",\"authorship\":{\"contributor\":\"0xF02EEfC88336c142Dee946B14b6Fc24539357871\",\"signingKey\":\"{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"w3W1Iz56Ods1rXzaZ9J_rx8sKSh2OMp3vT8HOkCvjXk\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"KxosKYVd-BzkNFm1UF25hdKbgapUQY_4YDTnM9pnzsk\\\"}\",\"signature\":\"Z7RbQjBogk1k3DSNbbzSy5PF263MTePHHmSsBXiX5U7d2injyKQeA-XVyp3I9eIoXfWFSo7Bh_xIGeMvWRrdHw\",\"signingKeySignature\":\"0xcc9a65200310a4a22c6e82de0fb57f1005d04ea580bc8b8d6b2b4b054ee85e625c3118b47a293ac6187bf1de9e24ae7d9a9b9c615bbdf9dbca5a54e008006c901b\",\"signingKeyMessage\":\"I authorize publishing on mirror.xyz from this device using:\\n{\\\"crv\\\":\\\"P-256\\\",\\\"ext\\\":true,\\\"key_ops\\\":[\\\"verify\\\"],\\\"kty\\\":\\\"EC\\\",\\\"x\\\":\\\"w3W1Iz56Ods1rXzaZ9J_rx8sKSh2OMp3vT8HOkCvjXk\\\",\\\"y\\\":\\\"KxosKYVd-BzkNFm1UF25hdKbgapUQY_4YDTnM9pnzsk\\\"}\",\"algorithm\":{\"name\":\"ECDSA\",\"hash\":\"SHA-256\"}},\"nft\":{},\"version\":\"12-21-2020\",\"originalDigest\":\"Ou06yHhWM4A1m8czKZcbYM7-_GS1nRSD55e-JqrLCEw\"}"